{{unreliable sources|date=December 2017}} {{Infobox officeholder |honorific-prefix = MPA |name = Arshad Ali |office = Member of the [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly]] |term_start = May 2013 |term_end = |office1 = |term_start1 = |term_end1 = |predecessor1 = |president1 = |primeminister1 = |successor1 = |constituency = [[Constituency PK-19 (Charsadda-III)|PK-19 (Charsadda-III)]] |nationality = Pakistani |party = [[Qaumi Watan Party]] |otherparty = |birth_date = |birth_place = |occupation = [[Politician]] |profession = }}
'''Arshad Ali''' ({{lang-ps|ارشد على}}) is a Pakistani politician hailing from [[Charsadda District, Pakistan|Charsadda District]], who is currently a member of the [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly]], belonging to the [[Qaumi Watan Party]]<ref name="Mr.Arshad Ali">{{cite web|url=http://www.pakp.gov.pk/2013/member/pk-19/|publisher=''www.pakp.gov.pk''|title=Mr.Arshad Ali|access-date=13 December 2017}}</ref><ref name="Mr Arshad Ali">{{cite web|url=http://kpktribune.com/index.php/en/kp-mpas/charsadda-mpas/mr-arshad-ali|publisher=''kpktribune.com''|title=Mr Arshad Ali|access-date=13 December 2017}}</ref>.
==Political career== Ali was elected as the member of the [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly]] on ticket of [[Qaumi Watan Party]] from [[Constituency PK-19 (Charsadda-III)|PK-19 (Charsadda-III)]] in [[Pakistani general election, 2013]]<ref name="MPA Arshad Ali">{{cite web|url=http://www.awamipolitics.com/mpa-arshad-alis-profile-and-contact-22831.html|publisher=''www.awamipolitics.com''|title=MPA Arshad Ali|access-date=13 December 2017}}</ref><ref name="Arshad Ali">{{cite web|url=http://www.zemtv.com/profile/arshadali/|publisher=''www.zemtv.com''|title=Arshad Ali|access-date=13 December 2017}}</ref>.
